00:02:17.650 --> 00:02:18.650
Roger: Eleven.

00:02:18.650 --> 00:02:19.650
It’s very serious.

00:02:19.650 --> 00:02:24.870
We are about to return to a pre-antibiotic
era where even basic surgeries and other medical

00:02:24.870 --> 00:02:29.930
procedures can lead to death by septicemia
or another untreatable bacterial pathogens.

00:02:29.930 --> 00:02:32.099
The history of antibiotics is relatively short.

00:02:32.099 --> 00:02:37.500
In 1928, Scottish Scientist Alexander Fleming
discovered penicillin, capable of killing

00:02:37.500 --> 00:02:39.790
bacteria.

00:02:39.790 --> 00:02:43.990
Scientists Howard Florey and Ernst Chain then
mass produced it in time for the use on Allied

00:02:43.990 --> 00:02:46.710
Forces during World War two - the first example.

00:02:46.710 --> 00:02:51.010
in which more soldier died in battle than
from infection.

00:02:51.010 --> 00:02:54.950
It drastically changed the world of modern
medicine and extended the average human lifespan

00:02:54.950 --> 00:03:01.220
significantly.

00:03:01.220 --> 00:03:03.730
Not many more antibiotics were developed since
then.

00:03:03.730 --> 00:03:07.480
Bryson: Now, why has the discovery of new
antibiotics kind of fallen by the wayside

00:03:07.480 --> 00:03:08.990
for the past 30 or 40 years?

00:03:08.990 --> 00:03:14.010
Roger: Developing new antibiotics is not the
most effective way to make a steady profit.

00:03:14.010 --> 00:03:20.090
If you make a new drug for asthma or diabetes,
that’s a drug which patients will take likely,

00:03:20.090 --> 00:03:21.820
every day for the rest of their lives.

00:03:21.820 --> 00:03:26.409
So from an economic perspective, drug companies
don’t have much incentive to develop new

00:03:26.409 --> 00:03:27.590
antibiotic drugs.

00:03:27.590 --> 00:03:33.370
As Fleming accepted his Nobel Prize in 1945,
he warned that the misuse and overuse of antibiotics

00:03:33.370 --> 00:03:37.560
could result in drug resistant bacteria and
he was right.

00:03:37.560 --> 00:03:43.810
Roger: if you put antibiotics into heavy use,
then eventually, bacteria will find a way

00:03:43.810 --> 00:03:45.330
to become resistant to those drugs.

00:03:45.330 --> 00:03:47.510
